# ICP — what you sell & who you target   (REQUIRED)
#
# Copy to context/icp.md and fill in. This is the single source of truth for what
# the pipeline is looking for. Briefs you type are interpreted *against* this file.

## Product / value proposition
<One paragraph: what you sell and the core value it delivers. Example shape:
"We sell a [category] that helps [buyer] [outcome] without [pain]. The wedge is
[differentiator]." Be concrete — this is what disambiguates a good-fit account
from a look-alike that isn't.>

## Target market segments (priority order)
1. <Primary segment — the accounts you most want. e.g. "Mid-market B2B SaaS,
   200–2,000 employees, with a dedicated RevOps function">
2. <Adjacent segment>
3. <Long-shot / expansion segment>

## Default geography
<e.g. DACH, North America, UKI. Used when a brief omits a geography. Region names
here should match keys in config/region-expansion.yaml if you rely on expansion.>

## Default seniorities
<e.g. Director, VP, CxO. The default seniority band when a brief omits one.>

## Seed / exemplar companies (for look-alike discovery)
<5–15 named accounts that are perfect fits. Discovery can find look-alikes from
these. e.g. Acme Corp, Globex, Initech>

## Anti-fit signals (optional but valuable)
<Quick gut-check disqualifiers: "too small (<50 employees)", "no [function]",
"already uses [incumbent we can't displace]". Hard exclusions go in exclusions.md.>
